      "message": "Currently, we\u0027re not doing anything on |cancel| beyond ensuring that the callbacks from EmulatorQtWindow are not called.\n\nIn the case of ApiInstaller, this worries me a little. If the user hit cancel, it was likely because she launched a HUGE install that was undead. If we dont really cancel the install, it\u0027ll block future attempts at installing. This will confuse the user.\n\nwdyt?\n\n\nAlso, shouldn\u0027t this also mInstallDialog.hide()?\nSince |cancel| doesn\u0027t really trigger a call to EmulatorQtWindow::installDone, currently hitting the cancel button will seem to have no effect to the user?",
